      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MATRIARCH DAISY (5) is racing well and deserves a win after clocking in second in all three starts so far this campaign, last time leading from this barrier and sticking on to be beaten less than 5m at Bendigo. Race fit now and gets her chance to break through. BETTOR PUNTER NZ (8) was well fancied when resuming but manners let him down. He'll be fitter for that and draws for a nice trail so is worthy of another chance. SWEETHEART DIOR (2) has come from tougher barriers in her two starts since a spell and wasn't too far off the placings either time. Building in fitness and draws to advantage. IM STARVING (6) draws a couple of spots wider but should be better for an encouraging resuming effort when she placed at Cranbourne.",
